{"id":30441,"title":"[Topical therapy of inflammatory dermatoses, pruritus and pain, as well as hyperhidrosis].","abstract":"In this review, substances suitable for the topical treatment of inflammatory dermatoses, pruritus, pain and hyperhidrosis are presented. Both non-specific and specific topical treatments are discussed with respect to their mode of action, indications and side effects; included are corticosteroids, calcineurin inhibitors, dithranol, coal tar, liquor carbonis detergens, vitamin D analogues, metronidazole, azelaic acid, retinoids, and benzoyl peroxide. Additionally, practical directions for the treatment of these common skin diseases are provided. ","date":"2014-03-13","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24500042","annotations":[{"name":"Coal tar","weight":0.920564,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coal_tar"},{"name":"Benzoyl peroxide","weight":0.905521,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benzoyl_peroxide"},{"name":"Metronidazole","weight":0.894932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metronidazole"},{"name":"Itch","weight":0.834549,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itch"},{"name":"Dithranol","weight":0.814008,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dithranol"},{"name":"Pain","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Corticosteroid","weight":0.78464,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corticosteroid"},{"name":"Vitamin","weight":0.75303,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vitamin"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.746593,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Vitamin D","weight":0.74408,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vitamin_D"},{"name":"Topical","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article